Again, 2. Pardon and forgiveneſſe of ſinne, and that as oft as it is committed is the matter of his prayer: We have an Advocate, as you heard. Alas,2. Pardon of ſin. upon the committing of any ſinne, if there were no more ſtrength to do them away then is in the praiers and tears of the godly, if all the guilt lay upon them to diſcharge, how inſupportable would it be? but there is no ſinne at any time committed by thee, if repented of and forgiven, but Chriſt hath praied that it may be forgiven thee: ſo then though there be weakneſſe, unbelief, and dullneſſe in thy praiers, yet there was no fault to be found 
